      "message": "(Not something to fix in this CL.)\n\nFWIW, it makes me uneasy to just to string matching against the task name -- it seems like it would be easy to have an unintended match. I\u0027d rather see e.g. model \u003d\u003d \"Pixel\" rather than has(\"Pixel\"), so that we have to explicitly change something if we want it to apply to Pixel2, etc. I\u0027d even prefer strings.Contains(gpu, \"Intel\") over has(\"Intel\").\n\nI almost think it would be better to list all task names where an exception applies, so that we can re-evaluate if we add a new task, but that\u0027s probably unmaintainable.",
